The paper discusses an economic model for predicting miner hash rate allocation in cryptocurrencies, which involves analyzing price data and inferred risk tolerance. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.EC (Computer Science and Economics), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). However, given the focus on economic modeling and risk analysis, cs.CR and cs.EC are the most likely categories, followed by cs.GT, cs.CY, and cs.DC.
